commitMessage:"Fix Name constructor failing with max length relative name and root origin\n\nThe Name constructor failed when passing a max-length (253 chars) relative name and Name.root as origin
commitDate:"2025-01-26 22:15:01":
while this name is technically allowed.

The failure was caused by the Name constructor having the local "absolute" variable wrongly set to false in this case. This change fixes this by updating this flag when the origin is present.

Previous to this fix the workaround was to pass a null origin and manually append the final dot (root) to the string: in this case the constructor would work (as demonstrated by the "ctor_max_length_abs" test.

With this change I've also added a few tests for these edge-cases.

(cherry picked from commit 84e0e2365ba533fbb247145bc44991ea4b401782)

Closes #289
"

commitMessage:"removed synchronization in Header::getID (#216)

* removed synchronization in Header::getID

Header::getID synchronized on a static field causing unnecessary locking
especially when the ID field didn't need to be generated. As per the
discussion in #215
commitDate:"2025-01-26 22:15:01": this was due to a desire to have the ID generation\r\nbe lazy
lastCommitId:"52b59baf12d1a0760ce63ad667:
which is no longer needed.

This commit changes the ID generation behavior so the ID is either
explicitly supplied to the constructor
mergeBranchCommitId:null}:
or generated by the constructor
using the same SecureRandom instance. This makes the getID method a
simple getter with no need for synchronization

* Header constructor - check that ID is in range

* fixed formatting"
